==English==
[[Image:Chess bishop 0970.jpg|thumb|A bishop (chess)]]

===Etymology===
From Old English '''[[bisceop]]''' < Latin '''[[episcopus]]''' ([[overseer]], [[supervisor]]) < {{AGr.}} '''{{polytonic|[[ἐπίσκοπος]]}}''' (episkopos) "overseer" < '''{{polytonic|[[ἐπισκοπέω]]}}''' (episkopeō) "I watch over" < '''{{polytonic|[[ἐπί]]}}''' (epi) "over" + '''{{polytonic|[[σκοπέω]]}}''' (skopeō) "I examine".

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈbɪʃəp/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A high ranking official in the Catholic church who governs a [[diocese]], or a similar official in other denominations and religions.
# {{context|Chess}} A piece that may be moved only diagonally.
# {{slang}} [[penis]] (see [[bash the bishop]]).

